The paper deals with the construction of bent functions, which are commonly studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The construction is based on quadratic forms, which are also studied in computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the generalization of previous work, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
